      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "725e5d7c35e3b3bd",
        "summary": "Multi-skill orchestrator streaming can miss the required two-section SSE done body for classifier-order queries",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA multi-domain query that classifies into two skills does not produce the expected SSE `done` event body within the test timeout. The reported contract is a final body with exactly two `## ` headings in classifier order.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:390-879` — `_wrap_with_skill_sections` and the streaming path that applies it.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:349-350` — `run_orchestrator_streaming` is consumed by the chat SSE route.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\ndef _wrap_with_skill_sections(body: str, query_skills: list[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Compose a multi-skill body with one ``## <Skill>`` heading per skill.\n\n    Implements the §CORE-CHAT-026 contract: the final markdown for a\n    multi-domain query MUST start with one ``## `` section per skill in\n    classifier order, followed by shared ``## Sources`` / ``## Follow-Up``\n    blocks emitted by the agent.\n\n    The body is split at any pre-existing ``## Sources`` or ``## Follow-Up``\n    heading; everything before becomes the per-skill body, partitioned\n    heuristically by paragraph break across the ordered skills. We always\n    emit the headings in classifier order so test_core_chat_026's order\n    assertion holds even when the upstream agent produced a single block.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re as _re\n\n    if not query_skills or len(query_skills) < 2:\n        return body\n    if not body or not body.strip():\n        return body\n\n    # Already has per-skill headings (agent did it)? leave alone.\n    existing_skill_headings = _re.findall(\n        r\"^##\\s+(.+)$\", body, flags=_re.MULTILINE,\n    )\n    expected = {_skill_section_title(s).lower() for s in query_skills[:2]}\n    got_first_two = {\n        h.strip().lower() for h in existing_skill_headings[:2]\n    }\n    if expected.issubset(got_first_two):\n        return body\n\n    ...\n\n    if final_state.get(\"composed_response\") == \"__FALLBACK__\":\n        ...\n        async for event in execute_query_streaming(...):\n            ...\n            if event_type == \"done\":\n                fallback_content = event.get(\"content\", \"\")\n                if is_multi_skill and fallback_content:\n                    fallback_content = _wrap_with_skill_sections(\n                        fallback_content, query_skills,\n                    )\n                    event = dict(event)\n                    event[\"content\"] = fallback_content\n            if event_type != \"search_start\":\n                yield event\n        ...\n        return\n\n    composed = normalize_output(final_state.get(\"composed_response\", \"\"))\n    if is_multi_skill and composed:\n        composed = _wrap_with_skill_sections(composed, query_skills)\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Run the chat SSE flow with a query that the classifier routes to two skills.\n2. Observe the streamed events until completion or timeout.\n3. Check the final `done` event body for the number and order of `## ` headings.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe SSE stream completes within the test timeout and the final `done` body contains exactly two `## ` headings, ordered according to the classifier output.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe test times out before any SSE event arrives, so the expected `done` body is never observed.\n\n## Last toucher\navivriftin5 on 2026-05-03\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py` contains both the fallback-agent and direct-A2A multi-skill composition paths.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` is the SSE entrypoint that forwards `run_orchestrator_streaming` events.\n- The bug record references `CORE-CHAT-026` and the multi-skill section composer contract.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Run the chat SSE flow with a query that the classifier routes to two skills."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Observe the streamed events until completion or timeout."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Check the final `done` event body for the number and order of `## ` headings."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "The SSE stream completes within the test timeout and the final `done` body contains exactly two `## ` headings, ordered according to the classifier output.",
        "actual_behavior": "The test times out before any SSE event arrives, so the expected `done` body is never observed.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py",
            "line_start": 390,
            "line_end": 879,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "def _wrap_with_skill_sections(body: str, query_skills: list[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Compose a multi-skill body with one ``## <Skill>`` heading per skill.\n\n    Implements the §CORE-CHAT-026 contract: the final markdown for a\n    multi-domain query MUST start with one ``## `` section per skill in\n    classifier order, followed by shared ``## Sources`` / ``## Follow-Up``\n    blocks emitted by the agent.\n\n    The body is split at any pre-existing ``## Sources`` or ``## Follow-Up``\n    heading; everything before becomes the per-skill body, partitioned\n    heuristically by paragraph break across the ordered skills. We always\n    emit the headings in classifier order so test_core_chat_026's order\n    assertion holds even when the upstream agent produced a single block.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re as _re\n\n    if not query_skills or len(query_skills) < 2:\n        return body\n    if not body or not body.strip():\n        return body\n\n    # Already has per-skill headings (agent did it)? leave alone.\n    existing_skill_headings = _re.findall(\n        r\"^##\\s+(.+)$\", body, flags=_re.MULTILINE,\n    )\n    expected = {_skill_section_title(s).lower() for s in query_skills[:2]}\n    got_first_two = {\n        h.strip().lower() for h in existing_skill_headings[:2]\n    }\n    if expected.issubset(got_first_two):\n        return body\n\n    # Strip the single-skill scaffolding (``## Answer`` head, free-floating\n    # ``## Details`` mid-block) so we don't emit them between the per-skill\n    # sections — the multi-skill contract puts skill bodies under their own\n    # ``## <Skill>`` heading.\n    body_stripped = _re.sub(\n        r\"^##\\s+Answer\\s*\\n?\", \"\", body, count=1, flags=_re.IGNORECASE,\n    )\n    body_stripped = _re.sub(\n        r\"^##\\s+Details\\s*\\n?\", \"\", body_stripped,\n        flags=_re.IGNORECASE | _re.MULTILINE,\n    ).strip()\n\n    # Split off the trailing ``## Sources`` / ``## Follow-Up`` blocks; we\n    # keep them as a single shared tail so the per-skill split only\n    # operates on the body itself.\n    tail_split = _re.search(\n        r\"^(##\\s+(?:Sources|Follow[- ]?Up|Follow-Up Questions|Suggested Follow-Up)\\b.*)$\",\n        body_stripped,\n        flags=_re.MULTILINE | _re.IGNORECASE,\n    )\n    if tail_split:\n        head = body_stripped[: tail_split.start()].rstrip()\n        tail = body_stripped[tail_split.start():].strip()\n    else:\n        head = body_stripped\n        tail = \"\"\n\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in _re.split(r\"\\n\\s*\\n\", head) if p.strip()]\n    titles = [_skill_section_title(s) for s in query_skills]\n    sections: list[str] = []\n\n    # Even split paragraphs across skills in classifier order. With a\n    # single paragraph and N skills, the first paragraph goes to skill 0\n    # and the rest get a placeholder line so the sections remain\n    # individually addressable. With many paragraphs, partition by\n    # round-robin block boundaries.\n    if not paragraphs:\n        for t in titles:\n            sections.append(f\"## {t}\\n_(no content for {t.lower()})_\")\n    elif len(paragraphs) <= len(titles):\n        # 1–N paragraphs across N skills: assign in order, fill missing.\n        for i, t in enumerate(titles):\n            if i < len(paragraphs):\n                sections.append(f\"## {t}\\n{paragraphs[i]}\")\n            else:\n                sections.append(f\"## {t}\\n_(no separate content for this skill)_\")\n    else:\n        # More paragraphs than skills: split as evenly as possible.\n        chunks = [[] for _ in titles]\n        per = max(1, len(paragraphs) // len(titles))\n        for i, p in enumerate(paragraphs):\n            idx = min(i // per, len(titles) - 1)\n            chunks[idx].append(p)\n        for t, ps in zip(titles, chunks):\n            sections.append(f\"## {t}\\n\" + \"\\n\\n\".join(ps))\n\n    out = \"\\n\\n\".join(sections)\n    if tail:\n        out = out + \"\\n\\n\" + tail\n    return out",
            "blame_author": "avivriftin5",
            "blame_date": "2026-05-03"
          },
