        "bug_id": "9b45545301a58201",
        "summary": "Async session title emission happens after the chat stream finishes, causing the SSE test to wait past completion and time out.",
        "description_md": "### Symptom\nThe chat SSE test times out at 30s because the main answer stream completes, but the `session_title` event is emitted only afterward.\n\n### Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:388-397` — the `session_title` event is yielded from the `finally` block after the assistant message is saved.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/chat_history/db.py:95-103` — session title persistence is separate from the streaming path.\n\n### Code snippet\n```python\n        finally:\n            if final_content:\n                append_message(session_id, \"assistant\", final_content)\n                await history_db.save_message(\n                    session_id, \"assistant\", final_content,\n                    insight_data=insight_data,\n                    tool_calls=tool_calls_collected if tool_calls_collected else None,\n                )\n\n            if is_new_session and final_content:\n                title = await _generate_title(query, user_email=user_email, session_id=session_id)\n                await history_db.update_session_title(session_id, title)\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'session_title', 'session_id': session_id, 'title': title})}\\n\\n\"\n\n            # Canonical SSE termination marker. Smoke clients (X-SMOKE-002 /\n            # 003) read until this sentinel; without it the stream looks\n            # half-open and they fail with \"never saw [DONE]\" even though the\n            # orchestrator finished cleanly.\n            yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\"\n```\n\n### Reproduction steps\n1. Start a new chat session that produces a non-empty final answer.\n2. Read the SSE stream until the assistant answer is complete.\n3. Continue waiting for the `session_title` event.\n4. Observe that the stream does not satisfy the test within the 30s timeout window.\n\n### Expected behavior\nThe main answer stream completes within the test timeout, and the `session_title` event arrives in the same request flow without delaying completion past the timeout.\n\n### Actual behavior\nThe `session_title` event is emitted only after the assistant content has already been finalized and persisted, so the stream remains open long enough for the test to time out.\n\n### Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-04-05\n\n### Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` also emits the `[DONE]` SSE sentinel in the same `finally` block.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/chat_history/db.py` contains the title update helper used by this path.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open a new chat session that produces a non-empty final answer."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Consume the SSE stream until the assistant answer is complete."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Keep waiting for the `session_title` event on the same connection."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Observe that the request exceeds the 30-second test timeout."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "The SSE response completes within the test timeout, and the session title event is observable without extending the stream past completion.",
        "actual_behavior": "The session title event is emitted after the assistant response has finished, keeping the stream open long enough for the test to time out.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py",
            "line_start": 388,
            "line_end": 397,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "        finally:\n            if final_content:\n                append_message(session_id, \"assistant\", final_content)\n                await history_db.save_message(\n                    session_id, \"assistant\", final_content,\n                    insight_data=insight_data,\n                    tool_calls=tool_calls_collected if tool_calls_collected else None,\n                )\n\n            if is_new_session and final_content:\n                title = await _generate_title(query, user_email=user_email, session_id=session_id)\n                await history_db.update_session_title(session_id, title)\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'session_title', 'session_id': session_id, 'title': title})}\\n\\n\"",
            "blame_author": "Evgeny Kagan",
            "blame_date": "2026-04-05"
          },
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/chat_history/db.py",
            "line_start": 95,
            "line_end": 103,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "async def update_session_title(session_id: str, title: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Update title without changing updated_at (used for LLM-generated titles).\"\"\"\n    async with get_db_session() as db:\n        await db.execute(\n            update(ChatSession)\n            .where(ChatSession.id == session_id)\n            .values(title=title)\n        )",
