      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "9ed6a6eb65a29730",
        "summary": "Orchestrator SSE emits heartbeat only after a 15-second timeout, not every 10 seconds while a graph node is silent.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nWhen the orchestrator stream stays idle for more than 15 seconds, the client sees a `heartbeat` event only after the timeout path runs. The reported behavior is a heartbeat every 10 s ±1 s during silence, with a 30 s timeout.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:620-627` — the streaming loop waits on `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout=15.0)` and emits `{\"type\": \"heartbeat\"}` only when that wait times out.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:628-630` — the surrounding exception path cancels the graph task on errors after the timeout loop.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n    graph_task = asyncio.create_task(graph.ainvoke(initial_state))\n    try:\n        while True:\n            try:\n                final_state = await asyncio.wait_for(asyncio.shield(graph_task), timeout=15.0)\n                break\n            except asyncio.TimeoutError:\n                yield {\"type\": \"heartbeat\"}\n    except Exception as e:\n        if not graph_task.done():\n            graph_task.cancel()\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Start a graph request that remains silent for longer than 15 seconds.\n2. Observe the SSE stream from the orchestrator.\n3. Wait through the idle period without any node output.\n4. Note when `heartbeat` events appear and when the request times out.\n\n## Expected behavior\nDuring a silent period, the stream emits `heartbeat` events at roughly 10-second intervals, with small jitter, and the overall request times out at 30 seconds.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe stream waits up to 15 seconds before emitting a `heartbeat`, so the keepalive cadence does not match the stated 10 s ±1 s behavior.\n\n## Last toucher\nGuy Keinan on 2026-04-30\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py` is the only file in this repo that emits the `heartbeat` event.\n- Related label: `timeout-suspected-stale`.\n- Nearby orchestrator flow code in the same file handles graph delegation, composition, and streaming lifecycle.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Start an orchestrator request whose graph execution stays idle for more than 15 seconds."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Watch the SSE stream for keepalive traffic."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe that the first `heartbeat` appears only after the 15-second timeout path runs."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Continue observing the request until it ends or times out."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "While a graph node is silent, the orchestrator stream emits `heartbeat` events every 10 s ±1 s and times out at 30 s.",
        "actual_behavior": "The orchestrator emits `heartbeat` only after a 15-second `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout=15.0)` timeout in the streaming loop.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py",
            "line_start": 620,
            "line_end": 627,
            "commit_sha": "e0b7c931641312fa82de23638f3941dedafbeec3",
            "snippet": "    graph_task = asyncio.create_task(graph.ainvoke(initial_state))\n    try:\n        while True:\n            try:\n                final_state = await asyncio.wait_for(asyncio.shield(graph_task), timeout=15.0)\n                break\n            except asyncio.TimeoutError:\n                yield {\"type\": \"heartbeat\"}",
            "blame_author": "Guy Keinan",
            "blame_date": "2026-04-30"
          }
        ],
