      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "beddb4f4b5111010",
        "summary": "Orchestrator SSE stream does not emit the full documented event vocabulary in all runs",
        "description_md": "### Symptom\nThe full SSE coverage probe times out while waiting to observe every documented event type across the suite. The documented vocabulary includes `search_start`, `tool_call`, `tool_result`, `token`, `personal_context`, `personal_context_applied`, `enrichment_complete`, `skills_loaded`, `flow_suggestion`, `skill_start`, `skill_end`, `skill_error`, `compose_start`, `done`, and `error`.\n\n### Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:568-570` documents only `search_start, tool_call, tool_result, token, done, error` as the event set.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:582-583` emits `search_start`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:774-776` emits `flow_suggestion` only when `final_state[\"flow_suggestion\"]` is present.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:798-804` consumes `enrichment_complete` internally and does not forward it.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:805-841` handles `done` and builds the final SSE envelope.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:1029-1041` emits the final `done` event.\n\n### Code snippet\n```python\n    \"\"\"Run the orchestrator graph and yield SSE-compatible events.\n\n    For fallback (generic) queries: delegates to the existing streaming agent.\n    For app-specific queries: delegates to app's A2A agent, then streams the composed result.\n\n    Event types match what chat_router.py and the frontend expect:\n      search_start, tool_call, tool_result, token, done, error\n    \"\"\"\n    from app.orchestrator.agent import execute_query_streaming\n    from app.providers.oauth_routes import get_manager\n    from app.profiles.store import get_profile_store\n\n    t0 = time.time()\n\n    profile_store = get_profile_store()\n    profile_context = profile_store.get_prompt_context(user_email) if user_email else \"\"\n\n    manager = get_manager(user_sub)\n    connected = manager.get_connected_providers()\n    yield {\"type\": \"search_start\", \"servers\": connected}\n\n    yield {\n        \"type\": \"tool_call\",\n        \"tool\": \"classify_intent\",\n        \"server\": \"orchestrator\",\n    }\n\n    initial_state: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"request_id\": str(uuid.uuid4()),\n        \"session_id\": session_id,\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"user_message\": query,\n        \"user_email\": user_email,\n        \"user_profile_context\": profile_context,\n        \"conversation_history\": [],\n        \"matched_apps\": [],\n        \"is_multi_app\": False,\n        \"intent_confidence\": 0.0,\n        \"intent_reasoning\": \"\",\n        \"query_skills\": [],\n        \"needs_personal_context\": False,\n        \"personal_entities\": [],\n        \"topical_keywords\": [],\n        \"search_terms\": [],\n        \"time_window_days\": 14,\n        \"app_results\": [],\n        \"pending_actions\": [],\n        \"composed_response\": \"\",\n        \"evidence_refs\": [],\n        \"suggested_actions\": [],\n        \"error\": None,\n        \"error_code\": None,\n        \"flow_suggestion\": None,\n    }\n```\n\n### Reproduction steps\n1. Run the SSE coverage probe that subscribes to the orchestrator stream.\n2. Exercise the suite of queries that is intended to cover the documented event vocabulary.\n3. Observe that the probe never sees at least one of the documented event types before timing out.\n\n### Expected behavior\nThe orchestrator SSE stream exposes every event type in the documented vocabulary at least once across the suite.\n\n### Actual behavior\nThe stream does not surface the full documented vocabulary during the probe run, so the coverage check waits until timeout.\n\n### Last toucher\navivriftin5 on 2026-05-03\n\n### Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py` contains the SSE event assembly logic.\n- Nearby event handling in the same file includes `skills_loaded`, `skill_start`, `skill_end`, `skill_error`, `compose_start`, `flow_suggestion`, and internal handling for `enrichment_complete`.\n- Label `timeout-suspected-stale` matches the observed timeout failure mode.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Run the SSE coverage probe that subscribes to the orchestrator stream."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Exercise the suite of queries intended to cover the documented event vocabulary."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe that the probe does not see at least one documented event type before timing out."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": null,
        "actual_behavior": null,
