      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "30e8a03ee43d6f8f",
        "summary": "Chat SSE stream emits `data:` frames but the probe times out before observing any event",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nFormat-conformance probe times out before any SSE event is observed from the chat stream.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:344-402` — `event_stream()` yields SSE frames for orchestrator events and ends with a `[DONE]` sentinel.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:354` — per-event SSE framing uses `data: {json.dumps(event, default=str)}\\n\\n`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:398-402` — stream termination marker is emitted after the assistant response is persisted.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n    async def event_stream():\n        final_content = \"\"\n        insight_data = None\n        tool_calls_collected: list[dict] = []\n        try:\n            async for event in run_orchestrator_streaming(\n                query, session_id, history,\n                user_sub=user_sub, user_email=user_email,\n                fault_inject_skills=fault_inject_skills_request,\n            ):\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps(event, default=str)}\\n\\n\"\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"tool_call\":\n                    tool_calls_collected.append({\"tool\": event.get(\"tool\", \"\"), \"server\": event.get(\"server\", \"\")})\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"tool_result\":\n                    for tc in tool_calls_collected:\n                        if tc[\"tool\"] == event.get(\"tool\") and tc[\"server\"] == event.get(\"server\"):\n                            tc[\"duration_ms\"] = event.get(\"duration_ms\", 0)\n                            tc[\"status\"] = \"done\"\n                            if event.get(\"tool_trace_id\"):\n                                tc[\"tool_trace_id\"] = event[\"tool_trace_id\"]\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"done\":\n                    final_content = event.get(\"content\", \"\")\n                    insight_data = event.get(\"insight_data\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            stream_trace = str(uuid.uuid4())\n            logger.error(\n                \"Chat stream error (trace_id=%s): %s\", stream_trace, e, exc_info=True,\n            )\n            user_msg = _safe_error_message(e, \"We hit an unexpected issue while answering. Please try again.\")\n            yield (\n                \"data: \"\n                + json.dumps({\n                    \"type\": \"error\",\n                    \"error_code\": \"chat_stream_failed\",\n                    \"user_message\": user_msg,\n                    \"message\": user_msg,\n                    \"trace_id\": stream_trace,\n                })\n                + \"\\n\\n\"\n            )\n        finally:\n            if final_content:\n                append_message(session_id, \"assistant\", final_content)\n                await history_db.save_message(\n                    session_id, \"assistant\", final_content,\n                    insight_data=insight_data,\n                    tool_calls=tool_calls_collected if tool_calls_collected else None,\n                )\n\n            if is_new_session and final_content:\n                title = await _generate_title(query, user_email=user_email, session_id=session_id)\n                await history_db.update_session_title(session_id, title)\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'session_title', 'session_id': session_id, 'title': title})}\\n\\n\"\n\n            # Canonical SSE termination marker. Smoke clients (X-SMOKE-002 /\n            # 003) read until this sentinel; without it the stream looks\n            # half-open and they fail with \"never saw [DONE]\" even though the\n            # orchestrator finished cleanly.\n            yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\"\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Open the chat SSE endpoint used by the format-conformance probe.\n2. Send a request that causes the orchestrator stream to run.\n3. Observe that the probe waits for an SSE event and eventually times out before any event is seen.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe stream presents observable SSE frames in the `event: <type>\\ndata: <json>\\n\\n` format and the probe receives at least one event before timing out.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe probe does not observe an event before timing out, even though the stream code emits `data:` frames and a final `[DONE]` marker.\n\n## Last toucher\navivriftin5 on 2026-05-03\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` also emits `data: [DONE]\\n\\n` as the stream terminator.\n- Nearby SSE responses in the same file use the same `data:` framing pattern for empty-query and access-denied cases.\n- Labels indicate a timeout-suspected stale issue.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open the chat SSE endpoint used by the format-conformance probe."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Send a request that causes the orchestrator stream to run."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe that the probe waits for an SSE event and eventually times out before any event is seen."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "The stream presents observable SSE frames in the `event: <type>\\ndata: <json>\\n\\n` format and the probe receives at least one event before timing out.",
        "actual_behavior": "The probe does not observe an event before timing out, even though the stream code emits `data:` frames and a final `[DONE]` marker.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py",
            "line_start": 344,
            "line_end": 402,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "    async def event_stream():\n        final_content = \"\"\n        insight_data = None\n        tool_calls_collected: list[dict] = []\n        try:\n            async for event in run_orchestrator_streaming(\n                query, session_id, history,\n                user_sub=user_sub, user_email=user_email,\n                fault_inject_skills=fault_inject_skills_request,\n            ):\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps(event, default=str)}\\n\\n\"\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"tool_call\":\n                    tool_calls_collected.append({\"tool\": event.get(\"tool\", \"\"), \"server\": event.get(\"server\", \"\")})\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"tool_result\":\n                    for tc in tool_calls_collected:\n                        if tc[\"tool\"] == event.get(\"tool\") and tc[\"server\"] == event.get(\"server\"):\n                            tc[\"duration_ms\"] = event.get(\"duration_ms\", 0)\n                            tc[\"status\"] = \"done\"\n                            if event.get(\"tool_trace_id\"):\n                                tc[\"tool_trace_id\"] = event[\"tool_trace_id\"]\n                if event.get(\"type\") == \"done\":\n                    final_content = event.get(\"content\", \"\")\n                    insight_data = event.get(\"insight_data\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            stream_trace = str(uuid.uuid4())\n            logger.error(\n                \"Chat stream error (trace_id=%s): %s\", stream_trace, e, exc_info=True,\n            )\n            user_msg = _safe_error_message(e, \"We hit an unexpected issue while answering. Please try again.\")\n            yield (\n                \"data: \"\n                + json.dumps({\n                    \"type\": \"error\",\n                    \"error_code\": \"chat_stream_failed\",\n                    \"user_message\": user_msg,\n                    \"message\": user_msg,\n                    \"trace_id\": stream_trace,\n                })\n                + \"\\n\\n\"\n            )\n        finally:\n            if final_content:\n                append_message(session_id, \"assistant\", final_content)\n                await history_db.save_message(\n                    session_id, \"assistant\", final_content,\n                    insight_data=insight_data,\n                    tool_calls=tool_calls_collected if tool_calls_collected else None,\n                )\n\n            if is_new_session and final_content:\n                title = await _generate_title(query, user_email=user_email, session_id=session_id)\n                await history_db.update_session_title(session_id, title)\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'session_title', 'session_id': session_id, 'title': title})}\\n\\n\"\n\n            # Canonical SSE termination marker. Smoke clients (X-SMOKE-002 /\n            # 003) read until this sentinel; without it the stream looks\n            # half-open and they fail with \"never saw [DONE]\" even though the\n            # orchestrator finished cleanly.\n            yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\"",
            "blame_author": null,
            "blame_date": null
          }
        ],
