        "bug_id": "3e83408ef88cdb0e",
        "external_id": "CORE-CHAT-031",
        "source_line_start": 189,
        "source_line_end": 192,
        "raw_title": "Structured SSE error event on access-denied",
        "raw_body": "- **What's broken:** Test forces an access-denied query and expects an SSE `event: error` whose data carries `{error_code, user_message, trace_id}`. The current implementation in `chat_router.chat` (lines ~310 in the post-fix branch) emits `{type: \"error\", error_code: \"access_denied\", user_message, message, trace_id}` correctly — **but** the iterator does not include the `event: error` SSE field-line, only `data:`. The Wave-D2 spec strengthened the requirement so the event line must be present too.\n- **Affected files (likely):** `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` (the access-denied early-return StreamingResponse — change from `data:` only to `event: error\\ndata: …\\n\\n`)",
        "hinted_priority": "P0",
        "hinted_assignee": null,
        "hinted_repos": [
          "_core"
        ],
        "hinted_components": [],
        "hinted_files": [
          "apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py"
        ],
        "labels": [
          "real-product-gap"
        ],
        "inherited_module": {
          "repo_alias": "_core",
          "branch": "2026-05-03_Auto_Fixes",
          "commit_sha": "b7801f5",
          "repo_url": null
