        "closed_section": false,
        "removed_fix_text": null,
        "affected_test_ids": []
      },
      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "3e83408ef88cdb0e",
        "summary": "Access-denied chat SSE response omits the required event: error field",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nAn access-denied chat request returns a streaming SSE payload with the error JSON in `data:`, but the stream does not include the required `event: error` line.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:314-319` — the access-denied early return in `chat_router.chat` builds a `StreamingResponse` for the denial path.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n        if not has_access:\n            denial_trace = str(uuid.uuid4())\n            return StreamingResponse(\n                iter([f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'error_code': 'access_denied', 'user_message': 'Access denied to this session', 'message': 'Access denied to this session', 'trace_id': denial_trace})}\\n\\n\"]),\n                media_type=\"text/event-stream\",\n            )\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Send a chat request for a session where the user lacks access.\n2. Observe the SSE response body.\n3. Check the first SSE frame for the denial response.\n4. Note that the frame contains `data:` with the error JSON, but no `event: error` field line.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe denial response is emitted as an SSE error event, with an `event: error` line and a `data:` line carrying `{error_code, user_message, trace_id}`.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe denial response emits only a `data:` line containing the error JSON, so the SSE frame is not tagged as an `error` event.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-03-25\n\n## Related\n- Nearby logic in `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` around the access check and streaming response path.\n- Bug label: `real-product-gap`.\n",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Send a chat request for a session where the user lacks access."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Observe the SSE response body."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Check the first SSE frame for the denial response."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Note that the frame contains `data:` with the error JSON, but no `event: error` field line."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": null,
        "actual_behavior": null,
