        "bug_id": "a2f3f2083e6aad17",
        "summary": "Tablet widths 768–1024px do not collapse the sidebar or reflow chat layout",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nOn tablet-sized viewports between 768px and 1023px, the frontend keeps the full sidebar layout instead of collapsing to the icon rail and reflowing the chat area.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/global.css:32-120` — layout rules for `.app-shell`, `.sidebar`, `.main-content`, `.sidebar-collapsed`, and `.route-layer--chat`.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/ChatPage.tsx:371-383` — chat page renders the two-column chat layout inside `.chat-layout`.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx:69-150` — sidebar markup includes both full-width navigation and the collapsed icon rail.\n\n## Code snippet\n```css\n.app-shell {\n  display: flex;\n  height: 100%;\n}\n\n.sidebar {\n  position: fixed;\n  top: 48px;\n  left: 0;\n  bottom: 0;\n  width: 220px;\n  transition: width 0.15s ease;\n  background: var(--surface);\n  border-right: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  overflow-y: auto;\n  overflow-x: hidden;\n  z-index: 50;\n}\n\n.sidebar--collapsed {\n  width: 48px;\n  align-items: center;\n  padding-top: 4px;\n  gap: 2px;\n}\n\n.main-content {\n  margin-left: 220px;\n  margin-top: 48px;\n  width: calc(100vw - 220px);\n  height: calc(100vh - 48px);\n  overflow: hidden;\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  transition: margin-left 0.15s ease, width 0.15s ease;\n}\n\n.sidebar-collapsed .main-content {\n  margin-left: 48px;\n  width: calc(100vw - 48px);\n}\n\n.route-layer {\n  flex: 1;\n  min-height: 0;\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n\n.route-layer--chat {\n  flex-direction: row;\n}\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Open the frontend in a browser.\n2. Resize the viewport to a tablet width between 768px and 1023px.\n3. Navigate to the chat view.\n4. Observe the sidebar and chat layout.\n\n## Expected behavior\nAt tablet widths in the 768px–1023px range, the sidebar is in its collapsed icon-only presentation and the chat area reflows to the narrower available width.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe stylesheet contains no tablet breakpoint gate for 768px–1023px, so the desktop sidebar layout remains in effect and the chat area does not switch to the tablet-collapsed presentation.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2025-03-24\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/chat/ChatHistory.tsx:492-504` — collapsed chat history UI.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/global.css:1223-1244` — chat history collapsed width rules.\n- CORE-MOBILE-001 appears to share the same responsive-layout root cause.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open the frontend in a browser."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Resize the viewport to a tablet width between 768px and 1023px."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Navigate to the chat view."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Observe the sidebar and chat layout."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": null,
        "actual_behavior": null,
        "code_references": [
