      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "41c4edc839afd6ab",
        "summary": "Swipe-right pin gesture is missing from the chat session list, so the frontend never triggers the pin action from touch input.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA swipe-right gesture on a chat session row does not trigger pinning. The UI only exposes pin through the explicit pin button, while the touch gesture path described by the bug record is absent.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/chat/ChatHistory.tsx:220-265` — session row rendering and action buttons; no touch gesture handler is wired into the row.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/chat/ChatHistory.tsx:431-435` — the existing pin action handler is mouse-driven and calls the pin API from a click path.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/api.ts:552-553` — the frontend pin API helper targets `PATCH /api/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/pin`.\n\n## Code snippet\n`apps/centralfrontend/src/components/chat/ChatHistory.tsx:431-435`\n```tsx\n  const handlePin = async (e: React.MouseEvent, id: string) => {\n    e.stopPropagation();\n    const prev = sessions;\n    setSessions(s => s.map(x => x.id === id ? { ...x, is_pinned: !x.is_pinned } : x));\n    try { await pinSession(id); }\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Open the chat history/session list in the frontend.\n2. Swipe a session row to the right on a touch device or touch-emulation environment.\n3. Observe whether the session becomes pinned and whether the pin request is sent.\n\n## Expected behavior\nA right-swipe on a session row results in the session being pinned and the frontend issuing the pin request for that session.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe session row does not react to the swipe-right gesture. Pinning is only reachable through the explicit pin button, and the touch gesture path remains unimplemented.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-04-06\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/chat/ChatHistory.tsx` contains the session list UI and pin button.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/api.ts` contains the pin-session API helper.\n- The bug record mentions a touch-gesture utility module, but no implemented swipe-right handler was found in the frontend code paths inspected.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open the chat history/session list in the frontend."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Swipe a session row to the right on a touch device or touch-emulation environment."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe whether the session becomes pinned and whether the pin request is sent."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "A right-swipe on a session row results in the session being pinned and the frontend issuing the pin request for that session.",
        "actual_behavior": "The session row does not react to the swipe-right gesture. Pinning is only reachable through the explicit pin button, and the touch gesture path remains unimplemented.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
