        "raw_title": "Long-press fork/delete",
        "raw_body": "- **What's broken:** Long-press on a flow card should open a fork/delete action sheet; the `POST /api/flows/{id}/fork` endpoint exists, the touch handler is unimplemented.\n- **Affected files (likely):** centralfrontend's flow card component.",
        "hinted_priority": "P3",
        "hinted_assignee": null,
        "hinted_repos": [
          "_core"
        ],
        "hinted_components": [],
        "hinted_files": [],
        "labels": [
          "real-product-gap"
        ],
        "inherited_module": {
          "repo_alias": "_core",
          "branch": "2026-05-03_Auto_Fixes",
          "commit_sha": "b7801f5",
          "repo_url": null
        },
        "closed_section": false,
        "removed_fix_text": null,
        "affected_test_ids": []
      },
      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "999657755d0bd2d6",
        "summary": "Flow cards lack the long-press fork/delete action sheet on mobile, so touch users cannot access those actions.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nLong-pressing a flow card on mobile does not open the fork/delete action sheet described by the product behavior. The card currently exposes only tap-driven controls in the gallery view.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx:468-520` — flow card markup in the gallery grid; no long-press/touch handler is wired on the card container.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx:330-363` — `handleFork` and `handleDelete` exist as action handlers, but they are only invoked from other UI paths.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx:485-490` — the visible card actions currently include only the favorite button in the header.\n\n## Code snippet\n```tsx\n          {/* Flow cards grid */}\n          <div className=\"sf-grid\">\n            {filteredFlows.map(flow => (\n              <div key={flow.flow_id} className={`sf-flow-card${isFeatured(flow) ? ' sf-flow-card--featured' : ''}`}>\n                {isFeatured(flow) && (\n                  <div className=\"sf-featured-badge\">{'\\u2B50'} Featured</div>\n                )}\n                <div className=\"sf-flow-card-header\">\n                  <span className=\"sf-flow-icon\">\n                    {FLOW_ICONS[flow.icon] || '\\u{1F916}'}\n                  </span>\n                  <div className=\"sf-flow-info\">\n                    <div className=\"sf-flow-name\">{flow.name}</div>\n                    <div className=\"sf-flow-meta\">\n                      {flow.category} &middot; {flow.steps.length} steps &middot; {flow.usage_count} runs &middot; by {flow.created_by.split('@')[0]}\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"sf-flow-actions\">\n                    <button\n                      className={`sf-fav-btn${flow.is_favorite ? ' sf-fav-btn--active' : ''}`}\n                      onClick={() => handleFavorite(flow.flow_id)}\n                      title={flow.is_favorite ? 'Remove favorite' : 'Add favorite'}\n                    >\n                      {flow.is_favorite ? '\\u2605' : '\\u2606'}\n                    </button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Open the central frontend flow gallery on a mobile device or touch emulator.\n2. Press and hold a flow card.\n3. Observe that no fork/delete action sheet appears.\n4. Compare with the expected mobile interaction for flow-card actions.\n\n## Expected behavior\nLong-pressing a flow card opens an action sheet that exposes fork and delete actions for that flow.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe flow card has no long-press/touch interaction wired to open any action sheet, so fork/delete are not reachable through the described mobile gesture.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-05-03\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx:330-363` contains the existing fork/delete handlers.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx:468-541` is the gallery card rendering area.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/global.css:4649-4651` begins the flow-card styling block.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open the central frontend flow gallery on a mobile device or touch emulator."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Press and hold any flow card."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe that no fork/delete action sheet appears."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "Long-pressing a flow card opens an action sheet with fork and delete actions.",
        "actual_behavior": "Long-pressing a flow card does not open any action sheet, and the card exposes no touch handler for that gesture.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralfrontend/src/views/SkillsFlowsPage.tsx",
            "line_start": 468,
            "line_end": 520,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "          {/* Flow cards grid */}\n          <div className=\"sf-grid\">\n            {filteredFlows.map(flow => (\n              <div key={flow.flow_id} className={`sf-flow-card${isFeatured(flow) ? ' sf-flow-card--featured' : ''}`}>\n                {isFeatured(flow) && (\n                  <div className=\"sf-featured-badge\">{'\\u2B50'} Featured</div>\n                )}\n                <div className=\"sf-flow-card-header\">\n                  <span className=\"sf-flow-icon\">\n                    {FLOW_ICONS[flow.icon] || '\\u{1F916}'}\n                  </span>\n                  <div className=\"sf-flow-info\">\n                    <div className=\"sf-flow-name\">{flow.name}</div>\n                    <div className=\"sf-flow-meta\">\n                      {flow.category} &middot; {flow.steps.length} steps &middot; {flow.usage_count} runs &middot; by {flow.created_by.split('@')[0]}\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"sf-flow-actions\">\n                    <button\n                      className={`sf-fav-btn${flow.is_favorite ? ' sf-fav-btn--active' : ''}`}\n                      onClick={() => handleFavorite(flow.flow_id)}\n                      title={flow.is_favorite ? 'Remove favorite' : 'Add favorite'}\n                    >\n                      {flow.is_favorite ? '\\u2605' : '\\u2606'}\n                    </button>\n                  </div>\n                </div>",
