      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "8781946182eae02a",
        "summary": "Dashboard widgets expose drag styling and a save-position API, but the frontend has no long-press drag wiring for rearranging widgets.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nThe dashboard shows widget cards with a drag-handle affordance in edit mode, but there is no long-press/drag interaction that actually reorders widgets in the centralfrontend UI.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/views/DashboardPage.tsx:235-259` renders `ResponsiveGridLayout` with `isDraggable={editing}` and `draggableHandle=\".widget-drag-handle\"`, but no long-press or drag-start wiring is present in the page logic.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/dashboard/WidgetCard.tsx:68-76` renders the visible drag handle (`GripVertical`) only as a static span.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/api.ts:409-415` contains the client call for `PUT/PATCH /api/dashboard/widgets/{id}/position`, showing backend support for position updates.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/dashboard/ARCHITECTURE.md:176-180` documents the widget position endpoint as part of the dashboard API.\n\n## Code snippet\n```tsx\n          <ResponsiveGridLayout\n            width={width}\n            layouts={layouts}\n            breakpoints={BREAKPOINTS}\n            cols={COLS}\n            rowHeight={ROW_HEIGHT}\n            isDraggable={editing}\n            isResizable={editing}\n            compactType=\"vertical\"\n            margin={[16, 16]}\n            containerPadding={[0, 0]}\n            onLayoutChange={handleLayoutChange}\n            draggableHandle=\".widget-drag-handle\"\n          >\n            {widgets.map(w => (\n              <div key={w.id}>\n                <WidgetCard\n                  widget={w}\n                  onRefresh={handleRefresh}\n                  onDelete={handleDelete}\n                  editing={editing}\n                />\n              </div>\n            ))}\n          </ResponsiveGridLayout>\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Open the dashboard in centralfrontend with at least one widget present.\n2. Enter edit mode.\n3. Long-press or drag the widget handle.\n4. Observe that the widget grid does not expose a wired rearrange interaction from the page logic.\n\n## Expected behavior\nIn edit mode, widget cards can be rearranged through the dashboard UI, and the new positions are captured for persistence through the widget position endpoint.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe page renders a drag handle and a position-update API exists, but the frontend page does not contain long-press/drag wiring for widget rearrangement beyond the static grid props.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-03-22\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/components/dashboard/WidgetCard.tsx` for the drag-handle UI.\n- `apps/centralfrontend/src/api.ts` for widget position persistence.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/dashboard/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the documented dashboard widget API.\n",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Open the dashboard in centralfrontend with one or more widgets loaded."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Switch the dashboard into edit mode."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Attempt to long-press or drag the widget handle to rearrange widgets."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Observe that the dashboard does not present a wired rearrange interaction from the frontend page logic."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "In edit mode, dashboard widgets can be rearranged from the frontend and the resulting positions are observable through the dashboard UI and position persistence flow.",
        "actual_behavior": "The dashboard UI shows a drag handle and edit-mode grid props, but no long-press/drag wiring is present in the frontend page logic, so widget rearrangement is not exposed as a working interaction.",
