      },
      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "1ea533a9c6192fdc",
        "summary": "Full-dispatch SME extraction times out before all six agent events complete",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA request that exercises all six pillars (Network, Storage, Power, Physical, Security, Operations) times out after 30 seconds instead of completing the expected `orchestrator_start` plus six `agent_start` and six `agent_end` events.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/agents/orchestrator_graph.py:480-527` — the orchestrator emits `orchestrator_start` and `agent_start` events for dispatched SMEs.\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/llm/calls/sme_extraction.py:1156-1165` — the SME extraction flow emits `agent_start` for all six categories immediately.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n    # Emit agent_start for all 6 immediately\n    for cat in SME_CATEGORIES:\n        yield {\n            \"type\": \"agent_start\",\n            \"agent_name\": SME_DISPLAY_NAMES[cat],\n            \"category\": cat,\n            \"deviation_count\": cat_counts.get(cat, 0),\n            \"done\": False,\n        }\n\n    # Run all 6 in parallel\n    threads = []\n    for cat in SME_CATEGORIES:\n        t = threading.Thread(\n            target=run_sme,\n            args=(cat,),\n            daemon=True,\n        )\n        threads.append(t)\n        t.start()\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Submit a request that contains deviations across all six pillars.\n2. Observe the SSE stream for the run.\n3. Wait up to 30 seconds for the full dispatch to finish.\n4. Note that the stream does not complete with six `agent_end` events in time.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe full-dispatch run completes within the test timeout and produces one `orchestrator_start`, six `agent_start`, and six `agent_end` events.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe full-dispatch run stalls long enough to hit the 30-second timeout before all six SME completions are observed.\n\n## Last toucher\nEvgeny Kagan on 2026-03-27\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/agents/orchestrator_graph.py` contains the orchestrator-side event emission for dispatched SMEs.\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/demo_mock.py` has a parallel mock flow with the same event vocabulary.\n- The bug record references a stale cassette or stack state for the six-SME parallel run.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Submit a request that contains deviations across all six pillars."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Observe the SSE stream for the run."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Wait up to 30 seconds for the full dispatch to finish."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Note that the stream does not complete with six `agent_end` events in time."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": null,
        "actual_behavior": null,
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "vibe_coding/centarb",
