      "stage": "uploaded",
      "parsed": {
        "bug_id": "4b7b6ec69d98158a",
        "external_id": "ARB-AUTH-001",
        "source_line_start": 284,
        "source_line_end": 290,
        "raw_title": "`arb:sme` cannot access ARB-type management endpoints",
        "raw_body": "- **What's broken:** Test asserts `arb:sme` calling `POST /arb-types` returns 403, but observed 201 Created with the new ARB type written to the DB. **The fix in A-2 set `_require_admin` to return 403 for non-admin authenticated users — but the route handler for `POST /arb-types` does not call `_require_admin`.** The Depends/router-level guard is missing on this specific endpoint family.\n- **What's needed:** Wrap `POST /arb-types`, `PUT /arb-types/{id}`, `DELETE /arb-types/{id}`, `POST /arb-types/generate-from-ppt`, `POST /arb-types/{id}/deviation-catalog/generate` with `Depends(_require_admin)` (or call it inline at the top of each handler the way `_require_admin` already supports). The spec is clear that anything in the ARB-type management family is admin-only.\n- **Affected files:** `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py` (the `@app.post(\"/arb-types\", …)` route and siblings)",
        "hinted_priority": "P0",
        "hinted_assignee": null,
        "hinted_repos": [
          "vibe_coding/centarb"
        ],
        "hinted_components": [],
        "hinted_files": [
          "apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py"
        ],
        "labels": [
          "real-product-gap"
        ],
        "inherited_module": {
          "repo_alias": "vibe_coding/centarb",
          "branch": "2026-05-03_Auto_Fixes",
          "commit_sha": "7cfb1e0",
          "repo_url": null
        },
        "closed_section": false,
        "removed_fix_text": "What's needed: Wrap `POST /arb-types`, `PUT /arb-types/{id}`, `DELETE /arb-types/{id}`, `POST /arb-types/generate-from-ppt`, `POST /arb-types/{id}/deviation-catalog/generate` with `Depends(_require_admin)` (or call it inline at the top of each handler the way `_require_admin` already supports). The spec is clear that anything in the ARB-type management family is admin-only.",
        "affected_test_ids": []
      },
      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "4b7b6ec69d98158a",
        "summary": "ARB-type management endpoints allow arb:sme users to create and modify ARB types instead of returning 403",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA non-admin authenticated user with role `arb:sme` can call ARB-type management endpoints and receive success responses. The bug record specifically reports `POST /arb-types` returning `201 Created` and writing a new ARB type to the database instead of `403`.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:2706-2715` — `POST /arb-types`\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:2735-2744` — `PUT /arb-types/{type_id}`\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:2766-2778` — `DELETE /arb-types/{type_id}`\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:2620-2635` — `POST /arb-types/generate-from-ppt`\n- `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:3630-3636` — `POST /arb-types/{type_id}/deviation-catalog/generate`\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n@app.post(\"/arb-types\", response_model=ArbTypeOut, status_code=201)\ndef create_arb_type(\n    payload: ArbTypeCreate, request: Request, session: Session = Depends(get_session)\n) -> ArbTypeOut:\n    \"\"\"Create an ARB type configuration.\"\"\"\n    _require_admin(request, session)\n\n    existing = session.query(ArbType).filter(ArbType.name == payload.name).first()\n    if existing:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=409, detail=\"ARB type already exists\")\n\n    arb_type = ArbType(\n        id=uuid.uuid4(),\n        name=payload.name,\n        description=payload.description,\n        status=payload.status,\n    )\n    session.add(arb_type)\n    session.commit()\n    session.refresh(arb_type)\n    arb_type.status = _normalize_arb_type_status(arb_type.status)\n    return arb_type\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Authenticate as a user whose role is `arb:sme`.\n2. Send `POST /arb-types` with a valid ARB type payload.\n3. Observe the HTTP response and the database state.\n4. Repeat with `PUT /arb-types/{id}`, `DELETE /arb-types/{id}`, `POST /arb-types/generate-from-ppt`, and `POST /arb-types/{id}/deviation-catalog/generate`.\n\n## Expected behavior\nARB-type management endpoints are admin-only. Non-admin authenticated users, including `arb:sme`, receive `403 Forbidden` and no ARB-type management action is performed.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe ARB-type management handlers are reachable by `arb:sme` callers and can return success responses such as `201 Created`, allowing ARB type creation and related management actions.\n\n## Last toucher\n`Guy Keinan` on `2026-05-03` (commit `c643ee6491c6adc4641869b6fca6cf2feda3eea9`)\n\n## Related\n- `_require_admin` is defined in `apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py:813-817` and is already used by other admin-only routes in the same file.\n- Nearby admin-gated routes include `/api/roles`, `/api/roles/{email}`, and other management endpoints in `main.py`.\n- Bug ID: `ARB-AUTH-003` is referenced in the `_require_admin` docstring as the admin/SME authorization spec.\n",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Authenticate as a user whose role is arb:sme."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Send POST /arb-types with a valid ARB type payload."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe the HTTP response and the database state."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Repeat with PUT /arb-types/{id}, DELETE /arb-types/{id}, POST /arb-types/generate-from-ppt, and POST /arb-types/{id}/deviation-catalog/generate."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": "ARB-type management endpoints are admin-only. Non-admin authenticated users, including arb:sme, receive 403 Forbidden and no ARB-type management action is performed.",
        "actual_behavior": "The ARB-type management handlers are reachable by arb:sme callers and can return success responses such as 201 Created, allowing ARB type creation and related management actions.",
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "vibe_coding/centarb",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py",
            "line_start": 2706,
            "line_end": 2715,
            "commit_sha": "c643ee6491c6adc4641869b6fca6cf2feda3eea9",
            "snippet": "@app.post(\"/arb-types\", response_model=ArbTypeOut, status_code=201)\ndef create_arb_type(\n    payload: ArbTypeCreate, request: Request, session: Session = Depends(get_session)\n) -> ArbTypeOut:\n    \"\"\"Create an ARB type configuration.\"\"\"\n    _require_admin(request, session)\n\n    existing = session.query(ArbType).filter(ArbType.name == payload.name).first()\n    if existing:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=409, detail=\"ARB type already exists\")",
            "blame_author": "Guy Keinan",
            "blame_date": "2026-05-03"
          },
          {
            "repo_alias": "vibe_coding/centarb",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centarb_backend/app/main.py",
            "line_start": 2735,
