      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "4e84eb745caa2220",
        "summary": "Single-chat trace fanout stalls before all documented trace tables are populated and joinable by trace_id",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA test that posts one chat and waits for rows in the documented trace tables times out after 30 seconds. The expected fanout is at least one row in each of the eight trace tables, all joinable by `trace_id`.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/classifier.py:193-195` seeds `classification.trace_id` before logging the classification trace.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:100-108` carries `classification_trace_id` out of classification state.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:858-860` passes `classification_trace_id` into the orchestrator-run logger.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:1050-1052` passes `classification_trace_id` into the final orchestrator-run logger.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py:340-392` persists `classification_trace_id` on `orchestrator_runs`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/models/orchestrator_run.py:35-42` defines the `classification_trace_id` and `trace_id` columns on `orchestrator_runs`.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\n        classification = IntentClassification(\n            app_id=parsed.get(\"app_id\", FALLBACK_APP_ID),\n            confidence=float(parsed.get(\"confidence\", 0.0)),\n            reasoning=parsed.get(\"reasoning\", \"\"),\n            entities=parsed.get(\"entities\", {}),\n            query_skills=[s for s in raw_skills if isinstance(s, str)],\n            needs_personal_context=bool(parsed.get(\"needs_personal_context\", False)),\n            personal_entities=personal_entities,\n            topical_keywords=topical_keywords,\n            search_terms=search_terms,\n            time_window_days=time_window_days,\n        )\n\n        ct_id = uuid.uuid4()\n        classification.trace_id = ct_id\n        fire_and_forget(log_classification_trace(\n            row_id=ct_id,\n            llm_run_id=run_id,\n            user_message=user_message,\n            app_id=classification.app_id,\n            confidence=classification.confidence,\n            reasoning=classification.reasoning,\n            entities=classification.entities,\n            query_skills=classification.query_skills,\n            session_id=session_id,\n            user_email=user_email,\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Start the stack with the observability tables present.\n2. Post a single chat message through the central backend.\n3. Wait for the test harness to observe rows in the eight documented trace tables.\n4. Observe that the wait exceeds 30 seconds and the test times out.\n\n## Expected behavior\nA single chat produces at least one row in each documented trace table, and the rows can be joined by `trace_id`.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe single-chat flow does not complete the full trace fanout within the test window, so the harness never observes the full set of joinable trace rows.\n\n## Last toucher\navivriftin5 on 2026-05-03\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/admin/llm_usage.py:513-583` joins `orchestrator_runs` to `classification_traces` via `classification_trace_id`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/models/orchestrator_run.py` is the central row tying the pipeline together.\n- The bug body references the C-17 trace_id propagation migration and the five trace models touched there.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Start the central backend with the observability schema loaded."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Submit one chat message through the normal chat path."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Wait for the test to detect rows in the eight documented trace tables joined by `trace_id`."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Observe that the wait reaches the 30-second timeout without the full set of rows appearing."
          }
        ],
