      "stage": "uploaded",
      "parsed": {
        "bug_id": "903cdcc9122bf8fd",
        "external_id": "X-OBS-005",
        "source_line_start": 379,
        "source_line_end": 383,
        "raw_title": "Fire-and-forget logging swallows DB outage",
        "raw_body": "- **What's broken:** With the audit DB intentionally unreachable, the chat should still return 200 SSE with a valid answer, and `orchestrator_runs` should be missing the row (drop, don't crash). Test times out before any event arrives.\n- **Hypothesis:** Stale stack — possibly the test's audit-DB-down fixture is leaving the audit DB connection in a bad state for the rest of the test session.\n- **Affected files (likely):** `apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py`, `apps/centralbackend/app/audit.py` (the fire-and-forget try/swallow blocks)",
        "hinted_priority": "P1",
        "hinted_assignee": null,
        "hinted_repos": [],
        "hinted_components": [],
        "hinted_files": [
          "apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py",
          "apps/centralbackend/app/audit.py"
        ],
        "labels": [
          "timeout-suspected-stale"
        ],
        "inherited_module": {
          "repo_alias": "_core",
          "branch": null,
          "commit_sha": null,
          "repo_url": null
        },
        "closed_section": false,
        "removed_fix_text": null,
        "affected_test_ids": []
      },
      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "903cdcc9122bf8fd",
        "summary": "Audit and LLM observability writes can block chat responses when the audit DB is unreachable, causing SSE timeouts instead of a 200 response.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nWith the audit DB intentionally unreachable, the chat request times out before any SSE event arrives. The expected observable outcome is a 200 SSE response with a valid answer, while `orchestrator_runs` has no inserted row.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py:44-51` — `fire_and_forget()` schedules background logging tasks and only handles `RuntimeError` from missing event loop.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py:342-453` — `log_orchestrator_run()` and `log_user_feedback()` perform async DB writes and swallow exceptions after awaiting `get_session()` / `flush()`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/audit.py:103-161` — `AuditMiddleware.dispatch()` and `log_action()` perform DB writes around request handling and swallow exceptions after the request has already been processed.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\nasync def log_orchestrator_run(\n    *,\n    session_id: str,\n    user_message: str,\n    request_id: str | None = None,\n    user_email: str | None = None,\n    message_id: str | None = None,\n    conversation_depth: int | None = None,\n    total_duration_ms: int | None = None,\n    classify_ms: int | None = None,\n    agent_ms: int | None = None,\n    compose_ms: int | None = None,\n    title_ms: int | None = None,\n    classification_trace_id: uuid.UUID | None = None,\n    route_taken: str | None = None,\n    app_id: str | None = None,\n    confidence: float | None = None,\n    tools_available: int | None = None,\n    tools_called: int | None = None,\n    tool_names: list[str] | None = None,\n    agent_iterations: int | None = None,\n    recursion_limit_hit: bool = False,\n    response_length: int | None = None,\n    has_insight_data: bool = False,\n    has_evidence_refs: bool = False,\n    has_suggested_actions: bool = False,\n    classifier_model: str | None = None,\n    agent_model: str | None = None,\n    skills_loaded: list[str] | None = None,\n    query_skills: list[str] | None = None,\n    had_error: bool = False,\n    error_stage: str | None = None,\n    error_message: str | None = None,\n    personal_context: dict | None = None,\n) -> uuid.UUID | None:\n    \"\"\"Write one orchestrator run capturing the end-to-end pipeline trace.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        row = OrchestratorRun(\n            session_id=session_id,\n            request_id=request_id,\n            user_email=user_email,\n            message_id=message_id,\n            user_message=user_message,\n            conversation_depth=conversation_depth,\n            total_duration_ms=total_duration_ms,\n            classify_ms=classify_ms,\n            agent_ms=agent_ms,\n            compose_ms=compose_ms,\n            title_ms=title_ms,\n            classification_trace_id=classification_trace_id,\n            route_taken=route_taken,\n            app_id=app_id,\n            confidence=confidence,\n            tools_available=tools_available,\n            tools_called=tools_called,\n            tool_names=tool_names,\n            agent_iterations=agent_iterations,\n            recursion_limit_hit=recursion_limit_hit,\n            response_length=response_length,\n            has_insight_data=has_insight_data,\n            has_evidence_refs=has_evidence_refs,\n            has_suggested_actions=has_suggested_actions,\n            classifier_model=classifier_model,\n            agent_model=agent_model,\n            skills_loaded=skills_loaded,\n            query_skills=query_skills,\n            had_error=had_error,\n            error_stage=error_stage,\n            error_message=error_message,\n            personal_context=personal_context,\n        )\n        async with get_session() as db:\n            db.add(row)\n            await db.flush()\n            return row.id\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\"Failed to log orchestrator run\")\n        return None\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Run the chat flow with the audit DB unavailable.\n2. Observe the request stream for the chat endpoint.\n3. Wait for the first SSE event.\n4. Check whether `orchestrator_runs` contains a row for the run.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe chat request completes with HTTP 200 and SSE output even when audit/observability storage is unavailable. The run record is absent when the DB write cannot complete.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe request stalls long enough for the test to time out before any SSE event is observed. The run record is not persisted when the DB is unreachable.\n\n## Last toucher\n- `llm_logging.py`: Evgeny Kagan on 2026-04-27\n- `audit.py`: Evgeny Kagan on 2026-04-27\n\n## Related\n- `CHANGELOG.md:484-489` documents the fire-and-forget observability behavior and the removal of FK constraints for independent background writes.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/admin/llm_usage.py:588-590` depends on `orchestrator_runs.created_at` being written at run end for trace queries.\n- Nearby observability models and admin trace queries are in `apps/centralbackend/app/admin/llm_usage.py`.\n",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Run the chat endpoint with the audit database intentionally unreachable."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Watch the SSE stream for the response."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Wait for the first event from the stream."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Inspect `orchestrator_runs` for the current run identifier."
          }
        ],
        "expected_behavior": null,
        "actual_behavior": null,
        "code_references": [
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py",
            "line_start": 44,
            "line_end": 51,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "def fire_and_forget(coro: Any) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Schedule a coroutine as a background task — caller never blocks on DB writes.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        task = asyncio.create_task(coro)\n        _background_tasks.add(task)\n        task.add_done_callback(_background_tasks.discard)\n    except RuntimeError:\n        logger.warning(\"fire_and_forget: no event loop — dropping log coroutine\")",
            "blame_author": null,
            "blame_date": null
          },
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/llm_logging.py",
            "line_start": 342,
            "line_end": 453,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "async def log_orchestrator_run(\n    *,\n    session_id: str,\n    user_message: str,\n    request_id: str | None = None,\n    user_email: str | None = None,\n    message_id: str | None = None,\n    conversation_depth: int | None = None,\n    total_duration_ms: int | None = None,\n    classify_ms: int | None = None,\n    agent_ms: int | None = None,\n    compose_ms: int | None = None,\n    title_ms: int | None = None,\n    classification_trace_id: uuid.UUID | None = None,\n    route_taken: str | None = None,\n    app_id: str | None = None,\n    confidence: float | None = None,\n    tools_available: int | None = None,\n    tools_called: int | None = None,\n    tool_names: list[str] | None = None,\n    agent_iterations: int | None = None,\n    recursion_limit_hit: bool = False,\n    response_length: int | None = None,\n    has_insight_data: bool = False,\n    has_evidence_refs: bool = False,\n    has_suggested_actions: bool = False,\n    classifier_model: str | None = None,\n    agent_model: str | None = None,\n    skills_loaded: list[str] | None = None,\n    query_skills: list[str] | None = None,\n    had_error: bool = False,\n    error_stage: str | None = None,\n    error_message: str | None = None,\n    personal_context: dict | None = None,\n) -> uuid.UUID | None:\n    \"\"\"Write one orchestrator run capturing the end-to-end pipeline trace.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        row = OrchestratorRun(\n            session_id=session_id,\n            request_id=request_id,\n            user_email=user_email,\n            message_id=message_id,\n            user_message=user_message,\n            conversation_depth=conversation_depth,\n            total_duration_ms=total_duration_ms,\n            classify_ms=classify_ms,\n            agent_ms=agent_ms,\n            compose_ms=compose_ms,\n            title_ms=title_ms,\n            classification_trace_id=classification_trace_id,\n            route_taken=route_taken,\n            app_id=app_id,\n            confidence=confidence,\n            tools_available=tools_available,\n            tools_called=tools_called,\n            tool_names=tool_names,\n            agent_iterations=agent_iterations,\n            recursion_limit_hit=recursion_limit_hit,\n            response_length=response_length,\n            has_insight_data=has_insight_data,\n            has_evidence_refs=has_evidence_refs,\n            has_suggested_actions=has_suggested_actions,\n            classifier_model=classifier_model,\n            agent_model=agent_model,\n            skills_loaded=skills_loaded,\n            query_skills=query_skills,\n            had_error=had_error,\n            error_stage=error_stage,\n            error_message=error_message,\n            personal_context=personal_context,\n        )\n        async with get_session() as db:\n            db.add(row)\n            await db.flush()\n            return row.id\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\"Failed to log orchestrator run\")\n        return None",
            "blame_author": null,
            "blame_date": null
          },
          {
            "repo_alias": "_core",
            "repo_url": null,
            "file_path": "apps/centralbackend/app/audit.py",
            "line_start": 103,
            "line_end": 161,
            "commit_sha": null,
            "snippet": "class AuditMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n    \"\"\"Logs every mutating request (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE) with user identity.\n\n    GET requests and high-frequency validation endpoints are skipped.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    async def dispatch(self, request: Request, call_next: RequestResponseEndpoint) -> Response:\n        path = request.url.path\n\n        if request.method == \"GET\":\n            return await call_next(request)\n        if path in _SKIP_PATHS or any(path.startswith(p) for p in _SKIP_PREFIXES):\n            return await call_next(request)\n\n        t0 = time.monotonic()\n        response = await call_next(request)\n        duration_ms = int((time.monotonic() - t0) * 1000)\n\n        email = _get_user_email(request)\n\n        try:\n            async with get_session() as db:\n                db.add(AuditLog(\n                    user_email=email,\n                    action=f\"http.{request.method}\",\n                    http_method=request.method,\n                    http_path=path,\n                    status=response.status_code,\n                    duration_ms=duration_ms,\n                    ip_address=_client_ip(request),\n                ))\n        except Exception:\n            logger.exception(\"Failed to write audit log for %s %s\", request.method, path)\n\n        return response",
            "blame_author": null,
            "blame_date": null
          }
        ],
