      "enriched": {
        "bug_id": "ec7e36a45a10ebbb",
        "summary": "Orchestrator chat streaming can exceed the 5s first-token latency budget and time out before any content is emitted.",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nThe performance probe reports that the first content token does not arrive within the 5 s p95 budget. The run times out at 30 s, so no first token is observed.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/agent.py:67-74` — the LLM is created with `streaming=True` and `max_tokens=4096`.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/agent.py:799-814` — the streaming loop waits on `agent.astream_events(...)` before any event is processed.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py:1-5` — the orchestrator graph routes requests through `load_context → classify_intent → [fallback | a2a_delegate] → compose_result → update_context → END`, so the first user-visible output depends on the downstream delegate/composer path.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\ndef _get_llm() -> ChatOpenAI:\n    return ChatOpenAI(\n        base_url=settings.CENTRAL_LLM_BASE_URL,\n        api_key=settings.CENTRAL_LLM_API_KEY,\n        model=settings.CENTRAL_LLM_MODEL,\n        temperature=0.1,\n        max_tokens=4096,\n        streaming=True,\n    )\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Start the central backend and open the chat path that uses the orchestrator.\n2. Send a message that triggers the orchestrator streaming response.\n3. Observe the SSE/chat stream timing.\n4. Note that no first content token arrives before the 5 s p95 threshold, and the request eventually times out around 30 s.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe first content token is observable within 5 s at p95 for the chat response stream.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe chat stream does not emit a first content token within the 5 s p95 budget, and the request times out before any content is seen.\n\n## Last toucher\navivriftin5 on 2026-05-03T00:14:00+03:00\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/agent.py` contains the streaming SSE loop for chat responses.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/graph.py` contains the request-routing graph that feeds the response path.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/personal_context.py` has a separate timeout budget for enrichment work, which is adjacent to the latency-sensitive chat path.\n",
        "reproduction_steps": [
          {
            "order": 1,
            "text": "Start the central backend and open the chat path that uses the orchestrator."
          },
          {
            "order": 2,
            "text": "Send a message that triggers the orchestrator streaming response."
          },
          {
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Observe the SSE/chat stream timing."
          },
          {
            "order": 4,
            "text": "Note that no first content token arrives before the 5 s p95 threshold, and the request eventually times out around 30 s."
          }
