        "bug_id": "9c6bbbb885f420d1",
        "summary": "Chat rate limiting hangs on the first request in the burst instead of returning responses within the 60-second boundary",
        "description_md": "## Symptom\nA burst test that posts 30 chat messages within 60 seconds does not complete; it times out around 30 seconds, and the first chat request in the burst appears to hang. The scenario also expects a 31st request to be rate-limited with `429` and `Retry-After`, then a later request after the window to succeed.\n\n## Where\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py:285-288` — `/api/chat` calls `check_chat_rate_limit(request)` before any chat handling.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/rate_limit.py:30-41` — in-memory sliding-window limiter for `/api/chat`, including the `len(hits) >= _CHAT_LIMIT` check and timestamp pruning.\n\n## Code snippet\n```python\ndef check_chat_rate_limit(request: Request) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Raise HTTP 429 if this IP has exceeded 30 requests/minute.\"\"\"\n    ip = _get_client_ip(request)\n    now = time.monotonic()\n    hits = [t for t in _chat_hits[ip] if now - t < _CHAT_WINDOW]\n    _chat_hits[ip] = hits\n    if len(hits) >= _CHAT_LIMIT:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=429,\n            detail=f\"Rate limit exceeded: {_CHAT_LIMIT} requests per {_CHAT_WINDOW}s\",\n        )\n    _chat_hits[ip].append(now)\n```\n\n## Reproduction steps\n1. Send 30 `/api/chat` requests from the same client within 60 seconds.\n2. Observe that each of the first 30 requests is expected to complete successfully.\n3. Send a 31st `/api/chat` request before the 60-second window expires.\n4. Wait until the 60-second window has passed.\n5. Send a 32nd `/api/chat` request.\n\n## Expected behavior\nThe first 30 requests complete successfully, the 31st request is rejected with HTTP 429 and a `Retry-After` response, and a later request after the window completes successfully.\n\n## Actual behavior\nThe burst test times out at about 30 seconds, with the first chat request in the burst appearing to stall instead of completing normally. The rate-limit path in the code only raises a 429 when the in-memory hit count reaches the limit; no `Retry-After` response is present in the shown limiter code.\n\n## Last toucher\nGuy Keinan on 2026-04-28\n\n## Related\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/orchestrator/chat_router.py` for the `/api/chat` entrypoint.\n- `apps/centralbackend/app/rate_limit.py` for the limiter logic.\n- Related label: `timeout-suspected-stale`.\n- Hypothesis in the bug record references X-PERF-002.",
        "reproduction_steps": [
